==English==
===Noun===
'''summit''' ([[summits]])

#(countable) a [[peak]]; the [[top]] of a [[mountain]]
#:''In summer, it is possible to hike to the '''summit''' of Mt. Shasta.''
#(countable) a [[gathering]] or [[assembly]] of [[leaders]]
#:''They met for an international '''summit''' on environmental issues.''

====Translations====
*Danish: [[top]] ''c'' (1), [[bjergtop]] ''c'' (1); [[topmøde]] ''n'' (2)
*Telugu: [[శిఖరాగ్రం]] (SiKaraagraM) (1), [[శిఖరాగ్ర సమావేశం]] (Sikharaagra samaavaeSam) (2)

===Verb===

# (''hiking/climbing'') To reach the summit of a mountain.

